def: A strong and offensive smell; rancidity. [R.] Bailey.
A phototheodolite, or a camera designed for use inphotogrammetry. --Pho`to*gram*met"ric (#), Pho`to*gram*met"ric*al(#), a.
To make French; to infect or imbue with the manners or tastesof the French; to Gallicize. Burke.
The federal council of the German Empire. In the Bundesrath andthe Reichstag are vested the legislative functions. The federalcouncil of Switzerland is also so called.
A poor person; especially, one development on private or publiccharity. Also used adjectively; as, pouper immigrants, pouper labor.
A cell annexed to an abbey, for the use of a hermit. Howell.
One who registers; a recorder; a keeper of records; as, aregistrar of births, deaths, and marriages. See Register, n., 3.
To decline or fail to prosecute; to allow to be dropped (saidof a suit); to enter judgment against (a plaintiff who fails toprosecute); as, the plaintiff was non-prossed.
A stone or fossil which has on it impressions or figures ofplants and animals.
A change of apparel; a second or different suit. [Obs.] Beau &Fl.
